I will make this again, but I couldn't give it 4 forks, especially as written - followed the recipe exactly and agree that it tastes pretty bland until you add the cilantro. I added 4 tablespoons of lime juice at the end to get a flavor that I liked. I used Frontera tomatillo + roasted serrrano & cilantro (Rick Bayless) which is rated medium. Next time, I will mince a serrano chile or two to kick it up. Clam juice supplied plenty of salt, if you use seafood stock, you will definitely need to correct for salt. I may try about 2 c clam juice and 2 c chicken broth and reduce it slightly to make the broth richer. Finally, I would skip the sun dried tomato and add some diced plum tomato instead.

