Rating: 0
This is my first review ever on Epicurious, but I made this delicious soup last night for dinner and had to weigh in! My boyfriend loved it and said it's definitely one to serve at a dinner party. Based on the reviews here and what I had at home, I followed the recipe but split the ingredients in half plus the following changes: used a whole can of hominy, a full 7 oz tin of Herdez brand Salsa Verde Mexicana Picante (in place of the tomatillo salsa) that I found in the "International" aisle of my grocery, peel of 1/2 lime, the liquid from a can of clams along with another cup of clam juice, then included the clams along w/ approx. 1/2 lb. frozen shrimp and 1/2 lb. bay scallops. I squeezed the 1/2 lime juice in at the end and added some cracked pepper. White pepper would have been even better. This was one of the easiest soups I have made. I served it with sides of rice made w/ onion + veggie stock and a green salad. Satisfying but not overly heavy. Just delicious...I only wish I had more left overs!

